  "body": "### Description\r\nBesu fails to import a block due to an invalid block error during BWS and then fails with an OutOfMemoryError.\r\n\r\nFrom the heap dump it looks like caused by [`emitBadChainEvent`](https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/ethereum/eth/src/main/java/org/hyperledger/besu/ethereum/eth/sync/backwardsync/BackwardSyncContext.java#L372) in  `BackwardSyncContext` accumulating a very large of blocks and headers. Doesn't look like we ever exit the loop.\r\n\r\ntop retained objects from the heap dump\r\n<img width=\"1226\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-11-03 at 4 47 59 pm\" src=\"https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/assets/909467/085c41a8-561b-4f25-bf25-fe8f0ea6879b\">\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\nI am able to recreate this in my test environment consistently by restarting the node. It is occurring on 3/4 of the fullsync goerli nodes.\r\n\r\nTested using build from https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/commit/a90e4487fc67f6d9315cf9499fda534490156f50\r\n",
